hh3cWIPS.description: This MIB provides information about WIPS feature. Wireless Intrusion Prevention System (WIPS) WIPS is designed to be employed in an area that is serviced by an existing wireless network. It aids in the early detection of malicious outsider attacks and intrusions via wireless networks, and takes corresponding measures in order to guarantee the wireless environment security.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleName.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleName
hh3cWIPSSigRuleName.description: Represents the name of signature rule.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleID.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleID
hh3cWIPSSigRuleID.description: Represents the ID of signature rule. The values from 1 to 32 are for built-in rules, which can not be assigned to user-define rules. When a user-define signature rule is being created, if ID is not specified, the ID of the rule will be automatically assigned, which values from 33 to 64. Once the rule is created, the ID is fixed and can not be changed again.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleRowStatus
hh3cWIPSSigRuleRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMatchAll.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMatchAll
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMatchAll.description: Represents whether match all the sub rules which have been configured in the signature rule. The default value for user-define rule is false, and for built-in rule is true.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctPeriod.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctPeriod
hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctPeriod.description: Represents the detect period of signature rule. Available value limits from 1 to 3600. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 60. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleTrackMethod.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleTrackMethod
hh3cWIPSSigRuleTrackMethod.description: Represents the track-method for the signature rule. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 'both(3)'.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerMAC.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerMAC
hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerMAC.description: Represents the detect threshold for per-MAC track-method. Available value limits from 1 to 32000. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 1000. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerSig.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerSig
hh3cWIPSSigRuleDctThresholdPerSig.description: Represents the detect threshold for per-Signature track-method. Available value limits from 1 to 32000. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 1000. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleActionEvtLevel.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleActionEvtLevel
hh3cWIPSSigRuleActionEvtLevel.description: Represents the level of event sended for the action of reporting event alarm. Available value limits from 0 to 7. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff.

hh3cWIPSSigRuleQuietTime.name: hh3cWIPSSigRuleQuietTime
hh3cWIPSSigRuleQuietTime.description: Represents the quiet time after reporting event alarm. Available value limits from 60 to 32000. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 900. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleFrameType.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleFrameType
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleFrameType.description: Represents the type of frame to match. 0x0 management type 0x1 control type 0x2 data type The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 'undo(3)'.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleFrameSubType.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleFrameSubType
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleFrameSubType.description: Represents the sub-type of frame to match. 1 association request 2 association response 3 probe request 4 beacon 5 disassoc 6 authentication 7 de-authentication The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 'none(0)'.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMac.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMac
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMac.description: Represents the MAC address or BSSID to match.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMacType.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMacType
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleMacType.description: Represents the type of MAC address or BSSID to match. 0 Source MAC address in the 802.11 frame header 1 Destination MAC address in the 802.11 frame header 2 BSSID field in the 802.11 frame header

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMin.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMin
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMin.description: Represents the minimun value of sequence number of packet to match. Available value limits from 0 to 4094. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMax.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMax
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSeqNumMax.description: Represents the maximum value of sequence number of packet to match. Available value limits from 1 to 4095. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMin.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMin
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMin.description: Represents the minimun value of SSID of packet to match. Available value limits from 0 to 31. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMax.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMax
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDLenMax.description: Represents the maximum value of SSID of packet to match. Available value limits from 1 to 32. The default value depends on the certain rule. For user-define rules it is 0xffffffff. The value 0xffffffff represents restoring default value operation.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSID.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSID
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSID.description: Represents the string of SSID of packet to match.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDOpe.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDOpe
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDOpe.description: Represents the compare way of the SSID in the sub rule, including include/not include/equal/not equal.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDCase.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDCase
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleSSIDCase.description: Represents the case sensitive or not for the SSID match. 'true': Case insensitive. 'false': Case sensitive.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternTable.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternTable
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternTable.description: The table defines the signature sub rules which define the user-define match way through pattern of packet.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternEntry.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternEntry
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each pattern signature sub rules.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternID.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternID
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternID.description: Represents the ID of the pattern sub rule.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleRowStatus
hh3cWIPSSigSubRuleRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternName.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternName
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternName.description: Represents the name of the pattern sub rule.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternOffset.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternOffset
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternOffset.description: Represents the offset value of packet match.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternMask.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternMask
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternMask.description: Represents the mask value of packet match.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMin.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMin
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMin.description: Represents the minimun value of match byte. Available value limits from 0 to 65534.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMax.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMax
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternValueMax.description: Represents the maximun value of match byte. Available value limits from 1 to 65535.

hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternFromPayload.name: hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternFromPayload
hh3cWIPSSigSubRulePatternFromPayload.description: Represents whether match start from the payload of the data frame.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyCfgSupportSet.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyCfgSupportSet
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyCfgSupportSet.description: Represents the bit string of supported countermeasure policy. The specific countermeasure policy is supported if its corresponding bit is set to 1; otherwise its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit3: misconfigured AP bit4: rogue AP bit5: unauthorized station bit6: external AP bit9: misassociation station bit10: potential authorized AP bit11: potential rogue AP bit12: potential external AP bit13: uncategorized AP bit14: uncategorized station

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyTable.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyTable
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for WIPS countermeasure policy. One policy could be assigned to different VSDs.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyEntry.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyEntry
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each countermeasure policy.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyName.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyName
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyName.description: Represents the name of countermeasure policy.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyCfgRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyCfgRowStatus
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyCfgRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyBitString.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyBitString
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyBitString.description: Represents the bit string of countermeasure policy configuration. The specific countermeasure of device is enabled if its corresponding bit is set to 1; disabled if its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit3: misconfigured AP bit4: rogue AP bit5: unauthorized station bit6: external AP bit9: misassociation station bit10: potential authorized AP bit11: potential rogue AP bit12: potential external AP bit13: uncategorized AP bit14: uncategorized station

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyFixedChl.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyFixedChl
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyFixedChl.description: Represents whether enable fixed channel scan function.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyRogueAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyRogueAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyRogueAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for rogue AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtRogueAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtRogueAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtRogueAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for potential rogue AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyMisconfAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyMisconfAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyMisconfAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for misconfigured AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyExternalAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyExternalAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyExternalAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for external AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtExternalAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtExternalAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtExternalAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for potential external AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUncateAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUncateAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUncateAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for uncategorized AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtAuthAPPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtAuthAPPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyPtAuthAPPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for potential authorized AP. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyMisassoStaPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyMisassoStaPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyMisassoStaPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for misassociated station. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUncateStaPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUncateStaPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUncateStaPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for uncategorized station. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUnauthStaPre.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUnauthStaPre
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyUnauthStaPre.description: Represents the precedence of countermeasure for unauthorized station. Available value limits from 0 to 9. Value 0xffffffff represents undo operation.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevListTable.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevListTable
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevListTable.description: The table defines the MAC address list of countermeasure device in WIPS countermeasure policy.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevListEntry.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevListEntry
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevListEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each MAC address of device.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevMAC.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevMAC
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevMAC.description: Represents the MAC address of countermeasure device.

hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevRowStatus
hh3cWIPSCtmPolicyDevRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctCfgLogSupportSet.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctCfgLogSupportSet
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctCfgLogSupportSet.description: Represents the bit string of supported malformed packet detect policy controlling the log function. The specific malformed packet detect policy is supported if its corresponding bit is set to 1; otherwise its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: invalid IE length bit1: duplicated IE bit2: redundant IE bit3: invalid packet length bit4: illegal IBSS and ESS bit5: invalid source address bit6: overflow EAPOL key length bit7: malformed authetication bit8: malformed association request bit9: malformed HT-IE bit10: large duration bit11: null probe response bit12: invalid deauthentication reason code bit13: invalid disassociation reason code bit14: overflow SSID length bit15: fata-jack bit17: invalid-channel

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctCfgTrapSupportSet.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctCfgTrapSupportSet
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctCfgTrapSupportSet.description: Represents the bit string of supported malformed packet detect policy controlling the trap function. The specific malformed packet detect policy is supported if its corresponding bit is set to 1; otherwise its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: invalid IE length bit1: duplicated IE bit2: redundant IE bit3: invalid packet length bit4: illegal IBSS and ESS bit5: invalid source address bit6: overflow EAPOL key length bit7: malformed authetication bit8: malformed association request bit9: malformed HT-IE bit10: large duration bit11: null probe response bit12: invalid deauthentication reason code bit13: invalid disassociation reason code bit14: overflow SSID length bit15: fata-jack bit17: invalid-channel

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyName.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyName
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyName.description: Represents the name of malformed packet detect policy.

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyCfgRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyCfgRowStatus
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyCfgRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyLogBitString.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyLogBitString
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyLogBitString.description: Represents the bit string of malformed packet detect policy controlling the log function configuration. The specific malformed packet detect is enbled if its corresponding bit is set to 1; disabled its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: invalid IE length bit1: duplicated IE bit2: redundant IE bit3: invalid packet length bit4: illegal IBSS and ESS bit5: invalid source address bit6: overflow EAPOL key length bit7: malformed authetication bit8: malformed association request bit9: malformed HT-IE bit10: large duration bit11: null probe response bit12: invalid deauthentication reason code bit13: invalid disassociation reason code bit14: overflow SSID length bit15: fata-jack bit17: invalid-channel

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyTrapBitString.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyTrapBitString
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyTrapBitString.description: Represents the bit string of malformed packet detect policy controlling the trap function configuration. The specific malformed packet detect is enbled if its corresponding bit is set to 1; disabled its corresponding bit is set to 0. bit0: invalid IE length bit1: duplicated IE bit2: redundant IE bit3: invalid packet length bit4: illegal IBSS and ESS bit5: invalid source address bit6: overflow EAPOL key length bit7: malformed authetication bit8: malformed association request bit9: malformed HT-IE bit10: large duration bit11: null probe response bit12: invalid deauthentication reason code bit13: invalid disassociation reason code bit14: overflow SSID length bit15: fata-jack bit17: invalid-channel

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyDurationThreshold.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyDurationThreshold
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyDurationThreshold.description: Represents the threshold of duration for large duration malformed packet detection.

hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyQuietTime.name: hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyQuietTime
hh3cWIPSMalPktDctPolicyQuietTime.description: Represents the quiet time after reporting event alarm.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListCfgTable.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListCfgTable
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListCfgTable.description: The table provides the OUI list of devices in the static trust list. WIPS will take the devices in the list as authorized devices.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListCfgEntry.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListCfgEntry
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each OUI in the static trust list.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListOUI.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListOUI
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListOUI.description: Represents the OUI in static trust list.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListRowStatus
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustOUIListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgTable.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgTable
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgTable.description: The table provides the vendor list of devices in the static trust list. WIPS will take the devices in the list as authorized devices.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgEntry.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgEntry
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each vendor in the static trust list.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListVendor.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListVendor
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListVendor.description: Represents the vendor in static trust list.

hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListRowStatus
hh3cWIPSStaticTrustVendorListRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cWIPSDctAPTable.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPTable
hh3cWIPSDctAPTable.description: The table represents the list of possible BSS information for APs detected by the WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPEntry.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPEntry
hh3cWIPSDctAPEntry.description: Each entry contains possible BSS information of each AP detected by WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPVSD.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPVSD
hh3cWIPSDctAPVSD.description: Represents the virtual security domain where the BSS was detected.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime
hh3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime.description: Represents the time since AP started to work, which is got from beacon/probe response frame.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRunTmLastUpdateTm.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRunTmLastUpdateTm
hh3cWIPSDctAPRunTmLastUpdateTm.description: Represents the time update hh3cWIPSDctAPRunningTime since system is up.

hh3cWIPSDctAPIsCountered.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPIsCountered
hh3cWIPSDctAPIsCountered.description: Represents whether the detected AP is countered by WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPWorkChannel.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPWorkChannel
hh3cWIPSDctAPWorkChannel.description: Represents the radio channel which the detected AP work on.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRadioType.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRadioType
hh3cWIPSDctAPRadioType.description: Represents the radio type used by the detected AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAuthMethod.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAuthMethod
hh3cWIPSDctAPAuthMethod.description: Represents the authentication method used by the detected AP. none(1) - No key management mode configured, psk(2) - pre-shared key authentication, dot1x(3) - 802.1x authentication, other(4) - other authentication, psk/dot1x(5) - psk and dot1x authentication, psk/other(6) - psk and other authentication, dot1x/other(7) - dot1x and other authentication, psk/dot1x/other(8) - psk, dot1x and other authentication.

hh3cWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod
hh3cWIPSDctAPEncryptMethod.description: Represents the encrypt method used by the detected AP. none(1) - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep(2) - WEP key, tkip(4) - WPA Temporal Key encryption, ccmp(8) - WPA AES CCMP encryption

hh3cWIPSDctAPSecurity.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPSecurity
hh3cWIPSDctAPSecurity.description: Represents the security suites of the detected AP. clear 0x01 wpa2 0x02 wpa 0x04 wep 0x08

hh3cWIPSDctAPSeverityLevel.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPSeverityLevel
hh3cWIPSDctAPSeverityLevel.description: Represents the severity level of the detected AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPLastDctTm.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPLastDctTm
hh3cWIPSDctAPLastDctTm.description: Represents the time that AP was detected for the last time since system is up.

hh3cWIPSDctAPFirstDctTm.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPFirstDctTm
hh3cWIPSDctAPFirstDctTm.description: Represents the time that AP was detected for the first time since system is up.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2BlackList.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2BlackList
hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2BlackList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as a rogue AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into hh3cWIPSBlockListTable and the category of the AP will be taken as rogue. If the value is false, the MAC address will be automatically deleted from hh3cWIPSBlockListTable.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2WhiteList.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2WhiteList
hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2WhiteList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as an authorized AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into hh3cWIPSTrustListTable. If the value is false, the MAC address will be automatically deleted from hh3cWIPSTrustListTable

hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2IgnoreList.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2IgnoreList
hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2IgnoreList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as an ignored AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into hh3cWIPSIgnoreListTable. If the value is false, the MAC address will be automatically deleted from hh3cWIPSIgnoreListTable

hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2CtmList.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2CtmList
hh3cWIPSDctAPAdd2CtmList.description: Represents whether the AP will be taken as a countered AP. If the value is true, the MAC address will be automatically added into hh3cWIPSCountermeasureListTable. If the value is false, the MAC address will be automatically deleted from hh3cWIPSCountermeasureListTable.

hh3cWIPSDctAPCategory.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPCategory
hh3cWIPSDctAPCategory.description: Represents the categorized result of the AP. For set operation, only the following values are valid: authorized(2),rogue(3),misconfigured(4),external(5)

hh3cWIPSDctAPCategoryWay.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPCategoryWay
hh3cWIPSDctAPCategoryWay.description: Represents by which way the AP is categorized. manual(1) -categorized by user autoByNMS(2) -categorized by NMS(Network Management System) autoByDev(3) -categorized by WIPS

hh3cWIPSDctAPStatus.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPStatus
hh3cWIPSDctAPStatus.description: Represents the status of the AP detected by WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPSSID.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPSSID
hh3cWIPSDctAPSSID.description: Represents the SSID broadcasted by AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaNum.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaNum
hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaNum.description: Represents the number of clients associated with the detected AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorNum.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorNum
hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorNum.description: Represents the number of sensors detecting the AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPVendor.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPVendor
hh3cWIPSDctAPVendor.description: Represents the vendor of this AP detected by WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaTable.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaTable
hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaTable.description: The table represents the list of station associated with APs detected by the WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaEntry.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaEntry
hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaEntry.description: Each entry contains possible station information detected by WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaMac.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaMac
hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaMac.description: Represents the MAC address of station associated with AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaRowStatus.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaRowStatus
hh3cWIPSDctAPAttachStaRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. It is read-only and will return 'Not writable' for set operation.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorTable.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorTable
hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorTable.description: The table represents the list of sensors.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorEntry.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorEntry
hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorEntry.description: Each entry contains possible sensor information of WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorRadioId.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorRadioId
hh3cWIPSDctAPRptSensorRadioId.description: Represents on which radio the sensor AP detected the AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPRptRSSI.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPRptRSSI
hh3cWIPSDctAPRptRSSI.description: Represents the current value of signal strength that WIPS sensor AP received from the AP.

hh3cWIPSDctAPLastRptTm.name: hh3cWIPSDctAPLastRptTm
hh3cWIPSDctAPLastRptTm.description: Represents the time that AP was detected by this sensor for the last time since system is up.

hh3cWIPSDctStaTable.name: hh3cWIPSDctStaTable
hh3cWIPSDctStaTable.description: The table represents the list of possible information for stations detected by the WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctStaEntry.name: hh3cWIPSDctStaEntry
hh3cWIPSDctStaEntry.description: Each entry contains possible station information of each station detected by WIPS.

hh3cWIPSDctStaVSD.name: hh3cWIPSDctStaVSD

hh3cWIPSDctNetworkCfg.name: hh3cWIPSDctNetworkCfg
hh3cWIPSDctNetworkCfg.description: Represents the encrypt method, security suite and authentication method which are used by the detected ESS. The lowest 8 bits mean encrypt method. The higher 8 bits mean security suite. The third 8 bits stand for authentication method. The higerest 8 bits are reserved. The meaning is shown as follows: 31 23 15 7 0 + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + | reserved | auth method | security suite|encryptmethod| + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + + For encrypt method, the following values are supported: 1: none - clear text or no cipher method is configure, 2: wep - WEP key, 4: tkip - WPA Temporal Key encryption, 8: ccmp - WPA AES CCMP encryption For security suite, the following values are supported: 0x01: clear 0x02: wpa2 0x04: wpa 0x08: wep For authentication method, the following values are supported: 1: none - No key management mode configured, 2: psk - pre-shared key authentication, 3: dot1x - 802.1x authentication, 4: other - other authentication, 5: psk/dot1x - psk and dot1x authentication, 6: psk/other - psk and other authentication, 7: dot1x/other - dot1x and other authentication, 8: psk/dot1x/other - psk, dot1x and other authentication.
